[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating commit metadata**\n\nI’m analyzing whether we should include untracked references in our commit. It seems like they might have been created previously and could complicate things. The task focuses on coverage, so adding unrelated metadata might not be beneficial. I wonder if the untracked file was generated by automation. I should check `git status` first. If it isn’t from our setup, it’s probably best to leave it out. Maybe looking at `git diff` could help further clarify.\n\n**Considering native image tests**\n\nI’m thinking about whether I need to test in a native image with a custom provider class. There's a concern that the native image may not support modifying the built-in provider, which ideally it should. I’m also considering dynamic access tracking and whether it only applies to non-constant class names. I need to ensure there are no compile errors with certain assertions I want to make. I’ll check dependencies and remember to handle deprecated classes accordingly.\n\n**Examining X509Store instantiation**\n\nI’m thinking I might not be able to create an X509Store instance with a null selector since our SPI would ignore it. That’s a good catch! There’s also a potential issue with class loaders where X509Util uppercases the algorithm, but our algorithm constants are already uppercase, so that's fine. I need to consider another possible issue with `Provider.put` triggering the provider service cache. Luckily, it seems like the selected bootstrap provider won’t cause any issues with a SecurityManager.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06b02a4b25360e7e0169ef3f33f58481a1864700624fbeb226\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp7z8_5iV84UxWTbsLE7SLwrhmS99-x9v2CHX80TYf0oS4slQNPGnoGmG8CIdESzoG7oio3aWYsp3gKHPFNCfKA6sm-mGrtMxIFsoUjYTHkhj24IRsuuNZsXfvP_uNG_gWm9rDVFqo-A7iimT0-7k3XPRXDISq435fnR1fwLgM95_67xTKKsYuhuAb1vVqg7hE4P7hJ5N2E5