 where X509Util uppercases the algorithm, but our algorithm constants are already uppercase, so that's fine. I need to consider another possible issue with `Provider.put` triggering the provider service cache. Luckily, it seems like the selected bootstrap provider won’t cause any issues with a SecurityManager.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DkMq94jzieXVEIG07tjEtY8N|fc_06b02a4b25360e7e0169ef3f3f69a481a181f21a5f27629888", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/build/native -type f | sed 's#^#/#' | grep -E 'reflect|metadata|reachability|agent-output|generated' | head -100", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 850, "output": 892, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31950, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777286962580, "responseId": "resp_06b02a4b25360e7e0169ef3f330c9481a1a46e15a4f93fb351"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_DkMq94jzieXVEIG07tjEtY8N|fc_06b02a4b25360e7e0169ef3f3f69a481a181f21a5f27629888", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/build/native/generated/generateTestResourcesConfigFile/resource-config.json\n/tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/bcprov-jdk18on-1.77/reflection-calls.json\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777286976019}]}
